<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="479" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">Conference files, lot 60 D 627, CF
                                    239</note>
                                <head>No. 479<lb/><hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation With
                                        Foreign Secretary <persName corresp="#p_EDENA1">Eden</persName>, by the Secretary of State, June 27,
                                        1954</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d479fn1">Drafted on June 29;
                                        copies of the source text were sent to Under Secretary
                                            <persName corresp="#p_SMITHWB1">Smith</persName>,
                                            <persName>Murphy</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BOWIERR1">Bowie</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MACARTHURDII1">MacArthur</persName>,
                                            <persName corresp="#p_ROBERTSONWS1">Robertson</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_BYROADEHA1">Byroade</persName>.</note></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi></seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1954-06-27">June 27, 1954</date>
                                    </dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>I mentioned the desirability of setting up one or more informal
                                    study groups which, on an unofficial basis, would consider some
                                    of the common problems of our countries, where there were major
                                    divergencies of policy.</p>
                                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EDENA1">Eden</persName> said he thought
                                    this matter needed to be thought over and he would think it
                                    over.</p>
                                <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">JFD</persName></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>